{
  "texts": [
    "Some models, such as DeepOlf (Sharma et al. 2020) and DeepNose (Shuvaev et al. 2024), mimic the structure and function of the olfactory bulb using convolutional or graph-based neural networks.",
    "These models replicate the spatial activation patterns of glomeruli in response to molecular inputs, improving prediction accuracy and reflecting biological realism.",
    "This connection between neuroscience and AI provides a valuable framework for modeling perception more effectively.",
    "Meta-heuristic algorithms have also shown potential in optimizing complex, multi-objective sensory tasks (Moshayedi et al. 2024a (Moshayedi et al., 2024b)).",
    "Evaluating the scalability of these algorithms can help address challenges such as computational efficiency and memory use."
  ]
}